summary: This is an FBI collected item log documenting the receipt of ten yearbooks from the FBI West Palm Beach Resident Agency on January 13, 2021. The yearbooks were collected during the 2006-2008 investigation into Jeffrey Epstein for child sex trafficking and contain child victim/witness identity information.

keyFacts: Ten yearbooks were collected by the FBI West Palm Beach Resident Agency on June 6, 2019, during the 2006-2008 investigation into Jeffrey Epstein.
The yearbooks contain child victim and child witness identity information, which is protected and restricted from disclosure.
The item was formally logged by the FBI on January 13, 2021, under case number SOD-NY-3027571.
The document is an FBI collected item log (FD-1087a) that tracks evidence in the Epstein investigation.
